posts.name: Max Arnold
posts.cooked:
I started trying to plan autos for our Week 3 competition in Kokomo, but this error keeps popping up for the path. Screenshot 2025-03-10 191437 1574×889 87.2 KB I have no idea as to why this error keeps showing up, my only idea is that PathPlanner is not integrated into our code, and can’t control the robot. I have uninstalled and reinstalled the gui, and the issue persists across devices when I update them through Git. I don’t know, can I get some help please. GitHub Repo is here: 1555_REEFSCAPE_2025

Screenshot 2025-03-10 191437 1574×889 87.2 KB

Screenshot 2025-03-10 191437 1574×889 87.2 KB
I think you should check what your next control value is set to(should be under waypoints)
Try changing your drive current limit to something like 200 or higher and update your wheel COF to be a higher number

posts.name: Max Arnold
posts.cooked: I don’t know what my control value actually does other than curving the path. I thought drive current limit was amps, and should be set to the same as what is configured on the Flexes. I updated COF though, from 1.1 to 1.2

posts.name: Max Arnold
posts.cooked: Please help, I found the problem parameter, what should my drive current limit be for NEO Vortex’s

I would change the current limit to be around 80A? Also check under the robot config setting and look for three question mark looking symbols that have values in Ms and make sure that NONE of those values are highlighted red(if the text color is white than it’s in an acceptable range for pathplanner)

posts.name: Max Arnold
posts.cooked: Sorry for not replying sooner, but this advice and some other factors solved the problem, one of which was that I had set a 3 inch radius rather than a 1.5 inch radius.
Also I’m curious, how and what did you do to your wheel radius?

posts.name: Max Arnold
posts.cooked: I had originally put in 3 inches but converted to metres, and I found out right before week 3 kokomo that it asked for radius, not diameter.
